IMPORTANT LEGAL NOTICES:

1. COMMUNICATIONS MONITORING LAWS

This software is designed for monitoring of radio communications. Users are
responsible for ensuring their use complies with all applicable laws and
regulations, including but not limited to:

- 18 U.S.C. ยง 2511 (United States - Interception of Communications)
- 47 U.S.C. ยง 605 (United States - Unauthorized Publication)
- Relevant state, local, and international laws

Generally speaking:
- Monitoring of public safety communications is legal in most jurisdictions
  for personal, non-commercial use
- Monitoring of cellular communications is ILLEGAL
- Intercepting and disclosing private communications may be ILLEGAL
- Using intercepted information for commercial advantage is ILLEGAL
- Interfering with communications is ILLEGAL

CONSULT A LAWYER if you are unsure about the legality of your intended use.

2. CODEC PATENTS

This software may interface with audio codecs that are covered by patents:

- IMBE (Improved Multiband Excitation) - Digital Voice Systems, Inc.
- AMBE (Advanced Multiband Excitation) - Digital Voice Systems, Inc.

The software authors make no claims regarding patent licensing. Users are
responsible for obtaining appropriate licenses or using alternative methods
(hardware decoders, etc.) as needed.

This software uses mbelib (https://github.com/szechyjs/mbelib) which provides
open-source implementations of these codecs. Patent applicability may vary
by jurisdiction and use case.

3. HARDWARE COMPATIBILITY

This software is designed to work with RTL-SDR and compatible devices. The
authors are not affiliated with Realtek or RTL-SDR manufacturers. RTL-SDR
dongles are typically sold for DVB-T reception; use for radio scanning is
at the user's discretion.

4. NO WARRANTY

This software is provided AS-IS with absolutely no warranty. The authors
assume no liability for:

- Legal consequences of use
- Equipment damage
- Data loss
- Interruption of service
- Any other damages or losses

5. RESPONSIBLE USE

Users of this software should:

- Respect privacy and communications laws
- Use for lawful purposes only
- Not interfere with communications
- Not disclose sensitive intercepted information
- Consider the ethical implications of monitoring

6. EXPORT CONTROLS

This software may be subject to export controls in some jurisdictions.
Encryption and communications software may be restricted. Users are
responsible for compliance with export laws.

